anslate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=en&tl=ru&u=http%3a%2f%2fSimplyDifferently%2eorg%2fTipi"><img src="imgs/flags/lang/ru.png" alt="" width=16 height=10 border=1 hspace=1 vspace=1> </a> </td><td valign=middle ><a href="http://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=en&tl=iw&u=http%3a%2f%2fSimplyDifferently%2eorg%2fTipi"><img src="imgs/flags/lang/iw.png" alt="" width=16 height=10 border=1 hspace=1 vspace=1> </a> </td></tr></table></div><div align=right><p>Page <b><font color=#c0c0c0>&lt;&lt; Prev</font></b> | <b><font color=#ff0000>1</font></b>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<b><a href="Tipi?page=1">2</a></b> | <b><a href=Tipi?page=1>Next &gt;&gt;</a></b></div><h1 class=header>Tipi</h1><table class=newsbox><tr><td><b>Updates</b><p><div style="height: 200px; overflow: auto;"><div class=newsitems><b>Sun, January 20, 2008</b>: Added three ways to seal a tipi off rain through the pole junction opening: hood, drip strip and ozan.
